{
  "id": "phekb-coronary-heart-disease-dx-and-procedure",
  "source": "phekb",
  "source_id": "coronary-heart-disease",
  "name": "CHD - Diagnosis + Procedure via _has (Interventional Subset)",
  "description": "**Cross-resource _has test combining Condition + Procedure.** Find CHD patients who have BOTH a CHD diagnosis AND have undergone a revascularization procedure (CABG or PCI). This is the interventional-management subset, distinct from medical-management-only patients. Tests whether LLM uses FHIR `_has` to combine diagnosis evidence with procedural evidence \u2014 a different cross-resource pairing than the more common Condition + MedicationRequest.",
  "prompt": "Find coronary heart disease patients who have BOTH a formal CHD diagnosis AND have undergone a revascularization procedure (CABG, PCI, coronary stent placement, or balloon angioplasty). The intent is the interventional-management cohort \u2014 patients whose CHD has been treated procedurally, not just medically.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find CHD patients with procedures.",
    "broad": "Find patients who have BOTH a coronary heart disease diagnosis AND have undergone a coronary revascularization procedure. Use FHIR `_has` to combine evidence from Condition and Procedure resources at the patient level.",
    "expert": "I need patients matching TWO criteria: a Condition with a CHD SNOMED code (53741008, 414545008, 233817007, 371803003, 371804009) AND a Procedure with a revascularization SNOMED code (232717009 CABG, 415070008 PCI, 36969009 stent, 68466008 balloon). Use `Patient?_has:Condition:patient:code=...&_has:Procedure:patient:code=...`. Note Procedure resources are typically scarcer than Condition or MedicationRequest in real EHRs \u2014 the diagnosis filter is necessary because some procedure codes also appear in screening contexts."
  },
